Class NoOpStorageProxy<T>

NoOpStorageProxy is an implementation of StorageProxy that does no operations. It silently absorbs and throws away all changes without creating any logging, warnings or any other visible behaviors or persistent changes.

It is aimed to be used by disabled particles to finish their job without causing any post-disabled async errors, etc.

TODO(sherrypra): Add a unit test to ensure this stays in sync with the real storage APIs
